Note: When-or with multiple integer literal alternatives. All three of 1/2/3
Note: should match the same body (return 100). 5 matches its own body (return 200).
Note: Anything else matches Otherwise (return 0).
Note: classify(1) + classify(2) + classify(3) + classify(5) + classify(99)
Note: = 100 + 100 + 100 + 200 + 0 = 500. 500 mod 256 = 244.
Note: Expected exit code: 244

Process called "classify" takes x as Integer returns Integer:
    Match x:
        When 1 or 2 or 3:
            Return 100
        When 5:
            Return 200
        Otherwise:
            Return 0
    End Match
    Return -1
End Process

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let r1 be classify(1)
    Let r2 be classify(2)
    Let r3 be classify(3)
    Let r4 be classify(5)
    Let r5 be classify(99)
    Return r1 plus r2 plus r3 plus r4 plus r5
End Process
